Male genitalia:
Median lobe sickle-shaped, narrow, simple; in ventral view, appearing somewhat flattened; in lateral view, apically tapering and strongly curved downwards (
Fig. 16B, C
). Shape of paramere broadly triangular, with weak, relatively short setae, mainly along dorsal margin of subdistal part (
Fig. 16D
).

Northern Queensland (Iron Range National Park at Cape York Peninsula) and south-eastern Papua New Guinea (Central Province) (
Fig. 28
).
